COVID-19 Status 💉 🦠

As of 3:51PM PT today, over 1.2 million Canadians have tested positive for COVID-19. Sadly, 12.4 thousand have died.

In the last day, new infections were reported and 0 deaths. Currently 661 are in the hospital and 165 are in the ICU. This is trending upwards.

Fortunately, 32 million doses of the vaccine have been administered. For those 5 years and older, 34.9% have their 1st shot and 33.1% are fully vaccinated!

Vaccination is slowing down, but there are 4 million doses in the freezer. It currently takes ~617 days for new deliveries to get into arms.

At the current rate, Canadians should achieve herd immunity around when 80% of the entire population is fully vaccinated. There is no approved vaccine for children under 5.

  • 80 in 100 have at least one vaccine dose,
    75 in 100 are fully vaccinated.
    36 in 100 have been boosted.
    Herd immunity is estimated at ~85%
